^B@2hondo717: The other guideline I like for takeout doubles is to have 4 cards in the unbid major(s). That works great if the opponents open a major, but if the opponents open a minor, it is less likely you will have 4 cards in both majors. I play if the opponents open a major, your takeout double should promise 4 cards in the other major. If they open a minor, you are allowed to have one 4 card major and one 3 card major -a total of seven card of both majors. So, because moe's hand is both slightly short of points, and slightly short of major suit cards, I would pass it. |
