^B@2hondo717: One of the kibs asked about Rule 20. Let me explain it now. The rule of 20 is one method, that I recommend, to determine if you have an opening hand. You take your HCP, plus the length of your 2 longest suits. If that adds up to 20, you have an opening hand. So, if you have 11 HCP, and a 5 card suit and a 4 card suit, that is 11 + 9 = 20
